Etymology[edit]

Literally "to lead a wife".

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈduː.koː ukˈsoː.rem/, [ˈd̪uː.koː ʊkˈsoː.rɛ̃ˑ]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈdu.ko ukˈso.rem/, [ˈd̪uː.kɔ ukˈsɔː.rɛm]

Verb[edit]

dūcō uxōrem (present infinitive dūcere uxōrem, perfect active dūxī uxōrem, supine ductum uxōrem); third conjugation, limited passive

  1. (of a woman) I marry; I take as a wife, I lead a wife home
  2. (in comic poets) I take prostitutes home
